  <original-body>Notifications currently will not be sent in the case of an error in the notified block.

This may or may not be desired, but I have use cases (transaction tracing) that would be better served by notification regardless of errors.

For example:

    ActiveRecord::Base.transaction do
      raise &quot;Error!&quot;
    end

Should state that there was a transaction, and that it took (some small amount of time).</original-body>
